## 📚 PHASE 0: RESEARCH & EXPERTISE BUILDING (CRITICAL - DO THIS FIRST)

Before touching ANY code, you MUST become an expert by researching and analyzing:

### 1. **Study Premium Beauty Editorial Mobile Design**
Search and analyze these websites on mobile:
- **Allure.com** - Editorial styling, article layouts, navigation patterns
- **Vogue.com** - Premium aesthetics, image treatments, typography
- **Net-a-Porter.com** - Luxury e-commerce, product grids, filtering
- **Glossier.com** - Gen-Z appeal, modern interactions, clean UI
- **Into The Gloss** - Beauty editorial, mobile-first content

**What to extract:**
- How do they handle hero sections on mobile? (height, text overlays)
- Grid layouts: 1 column? 2 columns? When do they switch?
- Navigation: Hamburger menu patterns, bottom nav usage
- Product cards: Aspect ratios, information density, touch targets
- Typography: Font sizes, line heights, heading scales on mobile
- Spacing: Padding, margins, section gaps
- Image treatments: Aspect ratios, loading strategies
- Animations: Subtle micro-interactions vs heavy effects
- Color schemes: Premium editorial palettes

### 2. **Mobile UI/UX Best Practices Research**
Study and internalize:
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44x44px (iOS) / 48x48px (Android)
- **Thumb zones**: Bottom 2/3 of screen is prime real estate
- **F-pattern reading**: Users scan in F-shape on mobile
- **Progressive disclosure**: Show essentials first, hide secondary content
- **Native gestures**: Swipe, pull-to-refresh, pinch-to-zoom
- **Safe areas**: Notch support for iPhone 12+
- **Performance**: Mobile users expect <3s load time
- **Responsive images**: Use srcset, lazy loading, WebP format

### 3. **Gen-Z & Women-Focused Design Trends**
Research current trends:
- **Editorial aesthetics**: Large imagery, elegant typography, white space
- **Trendy interactions**: Scroll-triggered animations, parallax (subtle)
- **Color psychology**: Feminine but not pink-overload, sophisticated palettes
- **Content discovery**: Endless scroll, related content, personalization
- **Social proof**: Instagram-style grids, user-generated content
- **Mobile shopping**: Quick view, save for later, seamless checkout

### 4. **Technical Mobile Optimization**
Understand:
- **Responsive breakpoints**: 375px (iPhone SE), 390px (iPhone 13), 430px (iPhone 14 Pro Max), 768px (tablet)
- **CSS Grid vs Flexbox**: When to use each for mobile layouts
- **Mobile-first CSS**: Start with mobile styles, enhance for desktop
- **Performance budgets**: Images <200KB, total page <2MB
- **Core Web Vitals**: LCP <2.5s, FID <100ms, CLS <0.1

